<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sheet1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sheet,</orth> subst. 1) any thing expanded: <cit><quote>such --s of fire,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 2, 46</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) a large piece of linen: <bibl n="shak. wt 4.3.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 3, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.3.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 3, 5</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.105" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.105" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 105</bibl> Used to shroud the dead: <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 103</bibl>. as a part of bed-furniture: <bibl n="shak. luc 472" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 472</bibl>. plur. <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 398" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 398</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.205" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 205</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.327" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 327</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.244" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 244</bibl> <cit><quote>(a pair of --s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.88" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 88</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.174" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 157</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.393" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 393</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.29" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.105" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 22</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 16</bibl>.
<lb />3) a broad piece of paper, as it comes from the manufacturer: <cit><quote>a s. of paper,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 138</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 138</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 50</bibl>.
<lb />Punning: <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 50</bibl>.
